Crowd currently supports user aliases, and Confluence could benefit from the same feature.  It would also offer another option for users to "change" their username in a sense, which currently can only be done with direct database manipulation.  

Example case:
Confluence connects to LDAP using the default of 'cn' for the User Name Attribute.  Two people in the LDAP have the same name, and therefore same 'cn,' but the duplicate isn't noticed by the Confluence admin until the wiki is well adopted.  The ability to alias would allow the admin to switch to a unique User Name Attribute and alias the old cn to prevent user pain.

