When a certain page contains a macro that is not found / enabled during migration, the normal process is to wrap the whole page in an unmigrated-wiki-markup macro. The page _will continue to work_ after the upgrade. 

However, our upgrade task reports these are *failures*: 

{code}
0 settings values failed.
0 PageTemplates failed.
224 ContentEntityObjects failed.
{code}

We need to distinguish between an actual failure of a batch vs. normal migration of a page to an unmigrated-wiki-markup block. 

We need to change the report here to stem support tickets that are raised because a customer thinks the upgrade has failed due to the failure count.

