Previously our Japanese customers can use double byte chars in Confluence User Macros.

But as of Confluence 3.4.x this was restricted to only a-z A-Z 0-9 _ and -, see CONFDEV-372 (restricted to Atlassian) and change set 123683. Saving a new user macros using Japanese characters will produce an error:
{noformat}
    User macro names can only contain the following characters: a-z, 0-9 and - 
{noformat}

Also, after upgrading to 3.4.x they had a nasty surprise that the admin console failed to display the characters correctly albeit they still can be used without any problem in their content.

